classNames.description: The class names for each DayPicker element.
classNames.name: classNames

modifiersClassNames.description: The class names for the day modifiers specified via `modifiers`.
modifiersClassNames.name: modifiersClassNames

styles.description: The inline styles for each DayPicker element.
styles.name: styles

modifiersStyles.description: The inline-styles for the day modifiers specified via `modifiers`.
modifiersStyles.name: modifiersStyles

initialMonth.description: The initial month to show in the calendar.
initialMonth.name: initialMonth

numberOfMonths.description:
The number of months to show in the date picker. See also `pagedNavigation`
and `reverseMonths`.
numberOfMonths.name: numberOfMonths

fromMonth.description: Allow navigation only after this month. See also `toMonth`.
fromMonth.name: fromMonth

toMonth.description: Allow navigation only before this month. See also `fromMonth`.
toMonth.name: toMonth

pagedNavigation.description:
When displaying multiple months, the navigation will be paginated
displaying the `numberOfMonths` months at time instead of one.
pagedNavigation.name: pagedNavigation

reverseMonths.description:
Render the months in reversed order. Useful when `numberOfMonths` is
greater than 1, to display the most recent month first.
reverseMonths.name: reverseMonths

month.description: The rendered month. Passing this props will make the component switch to controlled mode?: this means you will need to implement `onMonthChange` to enable months navigation.
month.name: month

fixedWeeks.description:
Display 6 weeks per months, regardless the monthâ€™s number of weeks. Outside
days will be always shown if setting this to `true`. See also
`showOutsideDays`.
fixedWeeks.name: fixedWeeks

showCaption.description: Show the month caption displaying the month and the year.
showCaption.name: showCaption

showHead.description: Show the month head containing the weekday names.
showHead.name: showHead

showOutsideDays.description:
Show the outside days. An outside day is a day displayed in a month but
falling in the next or the previous month. See also
`enableOutsideDaysClick`.
showOutsideDays.name: showOutsideDays

enableOutsideDaysClick.description: Enable click event for outside days. See also `showOutsideDays`.
enableOutsideDaysClick.name: enableOutsideDaysClick

showNavigation.description: Show the navigation bar. `onMonthChange` must be set.
showNavigation.name: showNavigation

prevLabel.description:
Label used for the previous month button in Navigation. Set it to empty
string to hide the button.
prevLabel.name: prevLabel

nextLabel.description:
Label used for the next month button in Navigation. Set it to empty string
to hide the button.
nextLabel.name: nextLabel

selected.description: Style the matching days as selected.
selected.name: selected

disabled.description: Disable the matching days. Disabled days cannot be clicked.
disabled.name: disabled

dir.description:
The text direction of the calendar. Use `ltr` for left-to-right (default)
or `rtl` for right-to-left.
dir.name: dir

formatDay.description: Format the content of the day element.
formatDay.name: formatDay

formatWeekdayName.description: Format the weekday's name in the head element.
formatWeekdayName.name: formatWeekdayName

formatWeekNumber.description: Format the week numbers (when `showWeekNumber` is set).
formatWeekNumber.name: formatWeekNumber

onDayClick.description: Event handler when the user clicks on a day.
onDayClick.name: onDayClick

onMonthChange.description:
Event handler when the month changes, e.g. when using the next/prev
navigation buttons.
onMonthChange.name: onMonthChange

onNextClick.description: Event handler when the next navigation button is clicked.
onNextClick.name: onNextClick

onPrevClick.description: Event handler when the prev navigation button is clicked.
onPrevClick.name: onPrevClick
